author: wrowe
msg: A new source to hide statics on Win32 that are purely internal.  They
may be bound to the libapr.lib but not exported, or in the static apr.lib,
but they are entirely for internal consumption.
This i18n fn is a helper to the startup code I'm hacking for libapr_app,
the static apr_app, and for apr's forthcoming apr_app_initialize() fn.

author: wrowe
msg: A companion patch to apr_dbg_file_handles.h so we can log them.

author: aaron
msg: Make apr_global_mutex_t work on systems w/o APR_HAS_THREADS.
If you don't have threads, you don't need to use cross-thread
mutual exclusion, so this becomes essentially apr_proc_mutex_t.
